    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static HiveMetastoreClientPool get(Properties properties,
                                          Optional<String> metastoreURI)
                                   throws IOException
        Get a HiveMetastoreClientPool for the requested metastore URI. Useful for using the same pools across different classes in the code base. Note that if a pool already exists for that metastore, the max number of objects available will be unchanged, and it might be lower than requested by this method.
        Parameters:
        properties - Properties used to generate the pool.
        metastoreURI - URI of the Hive metastore. If absent, use default metastore.
        Returns:
        a HiveMetastoreClientPool.
        Throws:
        IOException

        Returns:
        an auto returnable wrapper around a IMetaStoreClient.

      • safeGetClients

        public static HiveMetastoreClientPool.MultiClient safeGetClients(Map<String,HiveMetastoreClientPool> namedPools)
                                                          throws IOException
        A method to get multiple IMetaStoreClients while preventing deadlocks.
        Parameters:
        namedPools - A map from String to HiveMetastoreClientPool.
        Returns:
        a HiveMetastoreClientPool.MultiClient with a IMetaStoreClient for each entry in the input map. The client can be retrieved by its name in the input map.
        Throws:
        IOException
